      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FANTASTIC ADA (4) had a tricky draw last time and although midfield in fourth wasn't far away finishing 5 lengths from the winner (17.96). Strike rate this course and distance strong having won two of three tries. Can bounce back. TRENTINO (8) trailed the lead and fought on well to be beaten 2.25 lengths into third (22.67) at Warrnambool in a Bottom Up - Grade 5 over 390m. Hard to beat again. ESKIMO MOANA (1) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at this track behind Pinky Rocks (23.49) in a Other. Has a solid record from this box including two wins and a minor placing. Expected to be in this for a long way. MAGIC POPPY (2) gets a chance to improve on an unplaced run at her latest outing at this circuit.",
